The paper discusses a generalization of the local expression language used in Symbolic Probabilistic Inference (SPI) approach to inference in belief nets. This involves the use of operators to combine partial conditional distributions. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), computational linguistics (cs.CL), cryptography and security (cs.CR), and social and information networks (cs.SI).
